<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="4" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Porter</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-18"><hi rend="italic">January 18,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Porter reports that the minister for foreign affairs fully concurs
                            in the propositions contained in Department’s telegram of the 13th
                            instant, and that France desires no concession of territory in
                            China.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>